definition: variant of 為|为[wei4], because of/for/to
variant of 為|为[wei2]/as (i.e. in the capacity of)/to take sth as/to act as/to serve as/to behave as/to become/to be/to do
as (in the capacity of)/to take sth as/to act as/to serve as/to behave as/to become/to be/to do/by (in the passive voice)
to cross/to go over/to pass (time)/to celebrate (a holiday)/to live/to get along/excessively/too-

sentences.english: 'It is too early to make conclusions now, ' Mr. Hommen said.
sentences.chinese: 霍曼说，现在下结论还为时过早。

sentences.english: Comes face to face with an adversary the brave victory, now judges true brave to be also too early.
sentences.chinese: 狭路相逢勇者胜，现在来判断真正的勇者还为时过早。

sentences.english: I think it premature for us to discuss the question of agency.
sentences.chinese: 我以为现在会商代庖代理题目为时过早。

sentences.english: But it's far too early to talk about a hard landing in China.
sentences.chinese: 但是这还为时过早谈一谈在中国硬着陆。

sentences.english: But the expectation of new business is premature.
sentences.chinese: 但是对新业务的展望还为时过早了。

sentences.english: It is also still too early to forecast the impact of pictorial health warning (PHW) labels.
sentences.chinese: 预测图片健康警语标签的影响也为时过早。

sentences.english: It's too early to say what might be causing it.
sentences.chinese: 现在说是什么导致这一现象也许还为时过早。

sentences.english: Holmes says it's way too early to use this research in a court of law.
sentences.chinese: 霍姆斯说，在法院里使用基因研究结果还为时过早。

sentences.english: It's too early to dismiss the G-7 or G-8 as history.
sentences.chinese: G7或G8成为历史还为时过早。

sentences.english: But it's too early to project how much revenue that would generate, Woolsey said.
sentences.chinese: 但是，项目有多少收入将产生还为时过早，伍尔西说。

sentences.english: But that would be premature, Yeomans says.
sentences.chinese: 但是，约曼斯说，这还为时过早。

sentences.english: These are early days, so don't get carried away.
sentences.chinese: 然而说这些还是为时过早，因此不要得意忘形。

sentences.english: Emmett says it's premature to come down with a hard, regulatory hand.
sentences.chinese: 埃米特说，这是用硬，监管的手来还为时过早。

sentences.english: It's not too early to scope out a quiet place where you'll do your (dare we say it) studying.
sentences.chinese: 现在开始找一个安静的地方自习并不会为时过早。

sentences.english: It would be premature to forecast the outcome.

definition: don't pass judgment on a person's life until the lid is on the coffin (idiom)
to say again/to put off a discussion until later/moreover/what's more/besides
pressing in on one's eyelashes (idiom); imminent
to act with undue haste (idiom); eager and impatient/overhasty
